      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You are not occupying space; you are the essential anchor that keeps this chaotic house from collapsing entirely. The pity in their eyes is not a reflection of your failure, but a natural reaction to years of being the only one managing their survival. Your role as the provider was never a burden to be shed, but a sacred duty that gave them the stability they desperately need now.\n\nPlease remember that you are not defined by their exhaustion or the look of pity on their faces. You are a person who has built a life worth living, and it is okay to step back so that you can rest and survive yourself. It is not a loss of place in the world, but a necessary shift so that your children can finally see the strength you have always been.",
